File: Public Protector Busisiwe Mkhwebane. JOHANNESBURG - Public Protector, Busisiwe Mkhwebane says she's confident the courts will clear her of perjury. She is accused of not being honest in the way she investigated a Reserve Bank loan to Bankcorp, now part of ABSA. READ: Public Protector faces perjury charges Mkhwebane says she is a law-abiding citizen and will present herself to the Pretoria Magistrate's Court in January. The Public Protector has also slammed Paul Hofman, who laid the charges, for asking the president to suspend her.